                <head>No. 875<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Foreign Ministers of the United States, the United Kingdom, and France met in
                    Washington, July 10–14, to discuss a wide range of problems of mutual concern
                    including Austrian independence. For the records of these meetings, see <ref
                        target="frus1952-54v05p2#pg_1582">volume V, Part 2, pages 1582</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
